1 SENATE FLOOR VERSION
March 4, 2026
2
3 COMMITTEE SUBSTITUTE
FOR
4 SENATE BILL NO. 2180 By: Daniels
5
6
7 An Act relating to foreign lobbying; creating the
Foreign Principal Lobbying Oversight Act; providing
8 short title; defining terms; requiring agents of
foreign principals to make certain filing with the
9 Secretary of State; requiring filings to include
certain information; requiring agents to notify the
10 Secretary of State of changes; requiring a
termination notice in certain circumstances;
11 requiring the Secretary of State to publish certain
list; authorizing the Secretary of State to
12 promulgate certain rules; providing for exceptions;
providing for violations; providing for penalties;
13 providing for noncodification; providing for
codification; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
18 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
19 This act shall be known and may be cited as the “Foreign
20 Principal Lobbying Oversight Act”.
21 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
22 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 291.5 of Title 74, unless there
23 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
24 A. As used in this act:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2180 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. “Agent” means a person representing, acting, or lobbying for
2 compensation on behalf of a foreign principal to influence the laws,
3 policies, or regulations of this state or its political
4 subdivisions; secure funding or incentives for the benefit of a
5 foreign principal; or solicit, collect, or disburse contributions,
6 loans, or other funds on behalf of a foreign principal. Agent shall
7 not include:
8 a. diplomatic or consular officers, staff members of a
9 diplomatic or consular officer, or officials of a
10 foreign government,
11 b. attorneys representing a foreign country, government,
12 political party, or corporation or business entity
13 with a fifty-one percent (51%) or greater interest
14 that is owned by a foreign country, government, or
15 political party in purely commercial endeavors or
16 legal proceedings before state or federal courts,
17 agencies, or other political subdivisions, or
18 c. any news or press service or association or any
19 newspaper, magazine, periodical, or other publication;
20 and
21 2. “Foreign principal” means a foreign country, government,
22 high-ranking government official, political party, or business
23 entity with a fifty-one percent (51%) or greater interest that is
24
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2180 SFLR Page 2
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 owne d or controlled by a foreign country, government, high-ranking
2 government official, or political party.
3 B. Any agent for a foreign principal shall register and submit
4 a completed filing with the Secretary of State within fifteen (15)
5 days of becoming an agent for a foreign principal and pay a fee
6 pursuant to Section 1142 of Title 18 of the Oklahoma Statutes. A
7 completed filing shall include the identity of the agent and the
8 foreign principal compensating the agent, the beginning and ending
9 date, if known, of the agency agreement with the foreign principal,
10 the nature of the lobbying the agent is conducting for the foreign
11 principal, and any other information deemed necessary by the
12 Secretary of State.
13 C. An agent for a foreign principal shall notify the Secretary
14 of State within ten (10) business days of any changes to information
15 submitted pursuant to subsection B of this section. An agent shall
16 submit a termination notice with the Secretary of State within ten
17 (10) business days of ceasing representation for a foreign
18 principal.
19 D. The Secretary of State shall cause a list of registrations
20 and filings of agents for foreign principals submitted pursuant to
21 subsection B of this section to be published on its website and
22 shall periodically communicate to elected officials how to access
23 such list. The Secretary of State may promulgate rules and
24 procedures as necessary to effectuate the provisions of this act.
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB2180 SFLR Page 3
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 E. This act shall not apply to:
2 1. Religious or charitable organizations registered with the
3 Secretary of State or that are exempt from taxation pursuant to the
4 provisions of the Internal Revenue Code, 26 U.S.C., Section
5 501(c)(3);
6 2. Persons engaged in activities benefitting religious,
7 scholastic, academic, scientific, or fine arts interests; or
8 3. Persons involved in private and nonpolitical activities in
9 furtherance of a bona fide trade or commerce of the foreign
10 principal.
11 F. Any person who willfully or knowingly violates any provision
12 of this act, willfully or knowingly makes a false statement of any
13 material fact, or willfully or knowingly omits any material fact
14 required by this act shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a
15 misdemeanor and subject to a fine of Five Hundred Dollars ($500.00).
16 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
